@node HILL "Hillsea Lido"

The savegames are stored in Hillsea Lido's -S- -drawer. The name is
xMSAV-3 where x is the save position (1MSAV-3 if you saved at position 1
by pressing F1).

@endnode

@node SBII "Speedball II"

Speedball II saves a game to the bootblock of the savedisk. You'll have
to save the bootblock to a file (1024 bytes) to make use of this patch,
and write it back to the disk afterwards. There are many tools available
for this work (most virus-killers have an option to save the BB).

If you've got SB2 installed to HD, you won't have this problem :)


@endnode

